<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-23T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="1007" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1007">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.48/3205</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Guyant</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-23T13:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 23, 1916, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>You are authorized to send Porto Ricans on freighter to New Orleans, at
                            seventeen dollars each. Department will make necessary arrangements, and
                            take them to Porto Rico on transport after their arrival New
                            Orleans.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>